<H1>Vorbis Multimedia IOProc for OS/2 - 0.3.2</H1>
<P><A TITLE="Vorbis Multimedia IOProc for OS/2 - 0.3.2 " HREF="http://www.math.berkeley.edu/~roconnor/MMAudioPak/mmioVorb.html">MMIOVorbis
0.3.2</A> is
an MMIOProc for OS/2 that allows OS/2&#8217;s multimedia system to play
<A TITLE="xiph.org: Ogg Vorbis" HREF="http://www.xiph.org/ogg/vorbis/">Ogg Vorbis</A>
files.

</P>
<P>This IOProc supports translated read, traslated seek, and translated write operations.

</P>
<P>Ogg Vorbis decoding is done by <A TITLE="xiph.org: Ogg Vorbis" HREF="http://www.xiph.org/ogg/vorbis/">libvorbis</A>.

</P>
<P>Included is a example program called <CODE>bitrate</CODE> that prints the bitrate of an
Ogg Vorbis file. Also an encoder called <CODE>convert</CODE> that converts any MMOS/2 readable
file into an Ogg Vorbis file.

</P>
<H2>Download</H2>
<P>MMIOVorbis is part of the <A HREF="http://www.math.berkeley.edu/~roconnor/MMAudioPak/">MMAudio Pak</A>
When installing MMAudio Pak you can select which IOProcs to install.

</P>
<H2>Requirements</H2>
<P>MMIOVorbis requires the <A HREF="http://hobbes.nmsu.edu/cgi-bin/h-browse?sh=1&amp;dir=/pub/os2/dev/emx/v0.9d">EMX
runtime</A>.

</P>
<H2>Bugs and Known Issues</H2>
<P>MMIOVorbis does not support Ogg Vorbii that change audio parameters, such as sample rate
and number of channels, in the middle of the data.

</P>
<H2>To Do</H2>
<UL>
<LI>If requested I would consider adding support for untranslated Vorbii access.</LI>
<LI>The Ogg must be separated from the Vorbis.  Ogg is a container format, like RIFF, and 
MMOS/2&#8217;s compound file format support should be used here.  This separation would
allow MMOS/2 to support the Ogg FLAC format.</LI>
<LI>Decode using Tremor instead of libVorbis.</LI>
</UL>
